New Records: Immanuel Quickley scored 21 points and made 15 assists after missing the Raptors' last 22 games with a partially torn ulnar collateral ligament in his right elbow
Key Match Events: Toronto beat the Brooklyn Nets 130-113 to snap an 11-game losing skid
Quickley made the 29-foot shot to cap a 25-6 Raptors run in the fourth quarter
Pre-Game Insights: The Raptors (8-26) have not had their full starting lineup for a single game this season and Wednesday was no exception with swingman RJ Barret of Mississauga, Ont., out with an illness
Post-Match Reflections: Quickley was happy to be back playing with his teammates after missing 22 games
Raptors coach Darko Rajakovic emphasized the importance of Quickley's return to the team
Miscellaneous Highlights: RJ Barret's imminent return could help turn around Toronto's season
The Raptors would be joined by sophomore swingman Gradey Dick and centre Jakob Poeltl in the starting lineup if or when they are all healthy
Others: Immanuel Quickley averaged 18.6 points, 6.8 assists, and 4.8 rebounds — all career highs — in 38 games for Toronto last season
Quickley had 11 points, seven assists and a rebound in 17 minutes of play in the first half
